Package com.poesys.db.pk

Interface Summary
IPrimaryKey A generic interface for primary key classes that represent a set of columns and values that uniquely identify an object.
 

Class Summary
AbstractMultiValuedPrimaryKey Implements the IPrimaryKey interface for a key constructed from multiple values.
AbstractPrimaryKey An abstract implementation of the IPrimaryKey interface that is the parent of all the other primary key implementations, sharing code that all or most classes use.
AbstractSingleValuedPrimaryKey Implements the IPrimaryKey interface for a key constructed from a single value.
AssociationKeyMapping A helper class that represents the mapping of names in a list of foreign keys in an association.
AssociationPrimaryKey A concrete implementation of the IPrimaryKey interface that represents an association primary key.
CompositePrimaryKey A concrete implementation of the IPrimaryKey interface that represents a composite primary key.
GuidPrimaryKey Implements the IPrimaryKey interface for a key constructed from a single GUID value as a string.
IdentityPrimaryKey Implements the abstract single-valued primary key and the IPrimaryKey interface for a key constructed from a single integer value created by an identity or auto-increment column (a column that gets its value generated automatically when you insert and which you do not supply through the INSERT statement).
MessageKeyFactory This class is a factory that transforms a messaging DTO into a Poesys/DB primary key (IPrimaryKey).
NaturalPrimaryKey Implements the IPrimaryKey interface with a multi-valued column primary key comprising any number of arbitrary columns.
PrimaryKeyFactory A Factory Method pattern class containing factory methods for all the different kinds of primary keys.
SequencePrimaryKey Implements the single-valued primary key for a key constructed from a single integer value created dynamically from a SEQUENCE or some other, similar mechanism.
